BUA Foods Plc has announced a final dividend payment of N63 billion for the financial year ended December 31, 2021. The dividend payment which amounts to N3.50 per share, will be subject to shareholders’ approval at the Annual General Meeting (AGM) to be held on August 4, 2022 and appropriate withholding tax. According to the disclosure filed with the Nigerian Exchange (NGX), shareholders are to ensure their names are registered in the Register of Members by the qualification date of July 13, 2022. The company’s results showed that revenue rose by 72.8 per cent from N192.86 billion in the 2020 full year to N333.272 billion in 2021. Cost of sales increased to N230.312 billion from N129.287 billion, while gross profit stood at N102.960 billion as against N63.573 billion in 2020. Administrative expense stood at N10.422 billion from N4.013 billion, finance income for the period rose to N2.892 billion from N30.999 million, while finance cost jumped from N3.599 billion to N5.047 billion. Profit before tax increased to N77.468 billion from N47.249 billion, while net profit for the period under review amounted to N69.768 billion higher than N35.406 billion achieved in the corresponding period of 2020. Earnings per share was recorded as N4.24 kobo against N1.97 kobo recorded in the corresponding period of 2020. The Company’s total assets as at December 31, 2021 stood at N593.470 billion as against N374.320 billion. BUA Foods has 18 billion outstanding shares and a market capitalization of N1.07 trillion. Year-to-date, the company’s shares have appreciated by 48.75 per cent from N40.00 at the time of listing on January 5, 2022 to N59.50 as at April 14, 2022. BUA Foods was formed in November 2021 following a scheme of restructuring involving BUA Sugar Refinery Limited, IRS Flour Mills Limited, IRS Pasta Limited, BUA Rice Limited and BUA Oil Mills Limited, further to which BUA Sugar Refinery Limited emerged as the surviving entity. As part of the restructuring, the name of the enlarged entity was changed to BUA Foods Plc with its operations reorganised into five business divisions: Sugar, Flour, Pasta, Rice and Edible Oils. In December 2021, the company was converted into a public limited liability company and listed on the Nigerian Exchange on January 5, 2022. 